Architecture plan for issues #59-#68

Project shape
- Next.js App Router, React, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS academic personal site.
- Content remains centralized in `data/config.ts` with shared interfaces in `data/types.ts`.
- The redesign is presentation-only: no database, auth, API, or upload architecture is required.

Module structure and file organization
- `app/page.tsx`
  - Owns homepage section order. For #61 remove the standalone `AboutSection` from the homepage composition once its content is folded into `HeroSection`.
  - For #59/#67 reorder so `BlogsSection` renders last after `ServicesSection`.
- `app/globals.css`
  - Global base styles only. Keep global behavior such as focus states and reduced-motion handling here.
- `tailwind.config.ts`
  - Main theme-token work for #59: compact section spacing, thinner card borders, smaller card radius, and weaker/no shadows.
  - Preserve the existing `academic` palette names so components do not need broad semantic renames.
- `components/layout/header.tsx`
  - Main target for #60. Keep active route detection and external CV behavior, but restyle to compact reference layout.
- `components/layout/footer.tsx`
  - Main target for #68. Keep social link rendering; replace right-side profile tagline with the requested `Built with ❤️ and research.` copy.
- `components/layout/container.tsx`
  - Adjust vertical padding and max-width only if required by #59's global density change.
- `components/ui/card.tsx`
  - Main shared primitive for #59. Tune radius, border, padding, shadow, and hover treatment once so downstream section issues inherit the lighter style.
- `components/ui/section-heading.tsx` and `components/ui/view-all-link.tsx`
  - Keep common title/action pattern; tighten margins/gaps as part of #59 if needed.
- `components/sections/hero-section.tsx`
  - Main target for #61. Convert to three-zone layout: avatar left, identity/about/socials center, hero image right.
  - Reuse `profile.avatar`, `profile.heroImage`, `profile.bio`, `profile.researchIntro`, `profile.socials`, and `profile.cvHref` from `siteContent`.
- `components/sections/about-section.tsx`
  - Leave available for secondary reuse, but remove from homepage composition after #61 unless an issue explicitly deletes it.
- `components/sections/news-timeline-section.tsx`
  - Main target for #62. Convert from horizontal scroll cards to full-width vertical timeline with date column, blue dot/line, text area, dividers, and existing view-all link.
- `components/sections/education-awards-section.tsx`
  - Main target for #63. Render all `siteContent.education` and all `siteContent.awards` within the compact two-column section instead of only the first item.
- `components/sections/selected-publications-section.tsx`
  - Main target for #64. Keep selected-publication filtering, but render one compact row per paper with thumbnail/title/authors/venue and right-aligned resource links.
- `components/sections/experience-teaching-section.tsx`
  - Main target for #65. Preserve two columns; tighten the experience timeline and teaching icon list.
- `components/sections/services-section.tsx`
  - Main target for #66. Preserve three service groups; tune icon size, column dividers, item spacing, and list density.
- `components/sections/blogs-section.tsx`
  - Main target for #67. Convert from horizontal cards to a compact News-style date/title timeline list, and ensure homepage ordering places it after Services.

Shared types and data
- Existing content types in `data/types.ts` are sufficient for the requested redesign.
- Avoid data-shape changes unless a component needs an optional display field; if added, keep fields optional and update `data/config.ts` in the same issue.
- Static assets in `public/assets` remain repo-bundled; no user-upload or object-storage feature is planned for these issues.

Issue dependencies and sequencing
1. #59 should land first because it changes global spacing, card visual tokens, and homepage ordering assumptions used by every section.
2. #60 and #68 can be implemented independently after #59 because they affect the global shell.
3. #61 depends on #59 and should remove `AboutSection` from `app/page.tsx` while expanding `HeroSection`.
4. #62, #63, #64, #65, and #66 are independent section-level layout changes once #59 is in place.
5. #67 depends lightly on #59 for compact list styling and on final homepage order; implement after #66 if following the requested Blogs-last flow.

Key design decisions
- Keep the redesign component-scoped: prefer adjusting each existing section component over introducing a new layout framework.
- Keep all pages/server-rendered static where possible; no client state should be added except the existing theme toggle.
- Preserve accessibility semantics: headings, `time` elements, `aria-label`s, visible focus outlines, and meaningful link text.
- Preserve route behavior and existing `ViewAllLink` destinations.
- Use responsive CSS grids/flex layouts that collapse to a single column on mobile while matching compact desktop reference density.
- Avoid duplicating publication/blog/resource link logic where possible; if row layouts introduce repeated link pills, consider extracting small local helpers before adding broad new abstractions.

Verification strategy for each issue
- Run `npm run typecheck`, `npm run lint`, and `npm run build` after code changes.
- Smoke check `/` plus any affected list page links.
- For visual issues, inspect mobile and desktop widths and verify light/dark themes still have adequate contrast.
